Definition: strictly limiting the reference of a modified word or phrase
Example: the restrictive clause in `Each made a list of the books that had influenced him' limits the books on the list to only those particular ones defined by the clause
Synonyms: noun, cognition, grammar, c, strictly, the, reference, of, a, modified, word, or, phrase, restrictive, clause, in, Each, made, list, books, that, had, influenced, him, limits, on, to, only, those, particular, ones, defined, by
Category: adj.all
